<paragraph id="305A36B6E47CFFD2E0FF1867FA1CFD8A" blockId="4.[192,1440,547,667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<keyLead id="8B149583E47CFFD2E0FF1867FA1CFD8A" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
1. Elytra denticulate at shoulder; pronotum evenly, moderately closely punctured. Body brownishred. Length 5.0-6.0 mm. 
<collectingCountry id="48F27626E47CFFD2E25D1807FD00FD8A" box="[610,700,579,603]" name="Bolivia" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="48F27626E47CFFD2E2F81807FCF6FD8A" box="[711,842,579,603]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
............................ 
<taxonomicName id="F7E54D35E47CFFD2E4131800FA1CFD8A" authority="(Balthasar)" baseAuthorityName="Balthasar" box="[1068,1440,578,603]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Neotrichaphodioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forsterianus">
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E4131800FA1CFD8A" bold="true" box="[1068,1440,578,603]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E4131800FB40FD8A" bold="true" box="[1068,1276,578,603]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">N. forsterianus</emphasis>
(Balthasar)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="305A36B6E47CFFD2E0FF1820FA1CFD4A" blockId="4.[192,1440,547,667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<keyLead id="8B149583E47CFFD2E0FF1820FA1CFD4A" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
— Elytra not denticulate at shoulder; pronotum dually punctured. Body color, length and distribution variable ..................................................................................................................................... 
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E5AE18C7FA1CFD4A" bold="true" box="[1425,1440,643,667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">2</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="8B112E13E47CFFD2E0FF1887FA1CFCEA" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<paragraph id="305A36B6E47CFFD2E0FF1887FA1CFD2A" blockId="4.[192,1440,707,827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<keyLead id="8B149583E47CFFD2E0FF1887FA1CFD2A" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
2(1). Clypeus almost semicircular; genae obtusely rounded, slightly protruding beyond eyes. Body dark reddish brown. Length 5.0-5.5 mm. 
<collectingCountry id="48F27626E47CFFD2E2D618A7FCECFD2A" box="[745,848,739,763]" name="Ecuador" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
......................... 
<taxonomicName id="F7E54D35E47CFFD2E42118A0FA1CFD2A" authority="(Petrovitz)" baseAuthorityName="Petrovitz" box="[1054,1440,738,763]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Neotrichaphodioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecuadoriensis">
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E42118A0FA1CFD2A" bold="true" box="[1054,1440,738,763]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E42118A0FABEFD2A" bold="true" box="[1054,1282,738,763]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">N. ecuadoriensis</emphasis>
(Petrovitz)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="305A36B6E47CFFD2E0FF1940FA1CFCEA" blockId="4.[192,1440,707,827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<keyLead id="8B149583E47CFFD2E0FF1940FA1CFCEA" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
— Clypeus subtruncate anteriorly; genae distinctly protruding beyond eyes. Body color, length and distribution variable ................................................................................................................. 
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E5AE1967FA1CFCEA" bold="true" box="[1425,1440,803,827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">3</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="8B112E13E47CFFD2E0FF1927FA1CFC0A" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<paragraph id="305A36B6E47CFFD2E0FF1927FA1CFC4A" blockId="4.[192,1440,867,987]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<keyLead id="8B149583E47CFFD2E0FF1927FA1CFC4A" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
3(2). Posterior half of elytra with short, dense pubescence in males. Body piceous. Length 7.0-8.0 mm. 
<collectingCountry id="48F27626E47CFFD2E10719C0FECEFC4A" box="[312,370,900,923]" name="Peru" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Peru</collectingCountry>
......................................................................................... 
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E41D19C0FA1CFC4A" bold="true" box="[1058,1440,898,923]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName id="F7E54D35E47CFFD2E41D19C0FB53FC4A" authority="Dellacasa &amp; Dellacasa &amp; Skelley, 2010" authorityName="Dellacasa &amp; Dellacasa &amp; Skelley" authorityYear="2010" box="[1058,1263,898,923]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Neotrichaphodioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="woytkowskii" status="new species">
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E41D19C0FB53FC4A" bold="true" box="[1058,1263,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">N. woytkowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="19A257DFE47CFFD2E4C319C7FA1CFC4A" box="[1276,1440,899,923]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="305A36B6E47CFFD2E0FF19E0FA1CFC0A" blockId="4.[192,1440,867,987]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<keyLead id="8B149583E47CFFD2E0FF19E0FA1CFC0A" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
— Elytra glabrous in both sexes, at most with short, sparse pubescence before apex in males. Body yellowish to reddish brown. Length less than 6.0 mm. Widespread in South America .......... 
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E5AE1987FA1CFC0A" bold="true" box="[1425,1440,963,987]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">4</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="8B112E13E47CFFD2E0FF1E47FA1CFB6A" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<paragraph id="305A36B6E47CFFD2E0FF1E47FA1CFB8A" blockId="4.[192,1440,1027,1211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<keyLead id="8B149583E47CFFD2E0FF1E47FA1CFB8A" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
4(3). Elytral intervals distinctly convex, with short, sparsely pubescence preapically in males; superior apical spur of hind tibiae almost as long as first tarsal segment. Body reddish brown. Length 5.0-6.0 mm. 
<collectingCountry id="48F27626E47CFFD2E1F11E07FDA6FB8A" box="[462,538,1091,1115]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Brazil</collectingCountry>
................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="F7E54D35E47CFFD2E4A71E00FA1CFB8A" authority="(Harold)" baseAuthorityName="Harold" box="[1176,1440,1090,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Aphodius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volxemi">
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E4A71E00FA1CFB8A" bold="true" box="[1176,1440,1090,1115]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="0291EAA4E47CFFD2E4A71E00FA99FB8A" bold="true" box="[1176,1317,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">N. volxemi</emphasis>
(Harold)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="305A36B6E47CFFD2E0FF1E20FA1CFB6A" blockId="4.[192,1440,1027,1211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<keyLead id="8B149583E47CFFD2E0FF1E20FA1CFB6A" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
— Elytral intervals almost flat, glabrous in both sexes, superior apical spur of hind tibiae distinctly shorter than first tarsal segment. Body yellowish brown. Length 3.5-4.5 mm. 
<collectingCountry id="48F27626E47CFFD2E4801EC7FA87FB4A" box="[1215,1339,1155,1179]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="48F27626E47CFFD2E57B1EC7FA27FB4A" box="[1348,1435,1155,1179]" name="Bolivia" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="48F27626E47CFFD2E1071EE7FE39FB6A" box="[312,389,1187,1211]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="48F27626E47CFFD2E1B11EE7FDBFFB6A" box="[398,515,1187,1211]" name="Colombia" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="48F27626E47CFFD2E2331EE7FD36FB6A" box="[524,650,1187,1211]" name="Venezuela" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
........................................................ 
